{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fadb06cf-3b23-4c64-bc60-6ff44f3cfc5b","content":"Now I understand the project. Let me migrate it to xUnit.net v3.\n\nKey changes needed:\n1. `xunit` → `xunit.v3`\n2. `YTest.MTP.XUnit2` → `YTest.MTP.XUnit3`\n3. Add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` (v3 projects are executables)","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Vm2i8EyFgmcPaCxeRNJyj3","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating to xUnit v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01WBdHxmJqQ2WDF2MXmxJ3Yt","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-51bfba1afff845b7ad97cec148126570/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>\n    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"YTest.MTP.XUnit2\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>\n    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"YTest.MTP.XUnit3\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-51bfba1afff845b7ad97cec148126570/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"5dceb42d-85b4-435b-bc4f-030eac3f426b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. It's a simple xUnit.net v2 test project. I need to migrate it to xUnit.net v3. Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **TestProject.csproj**:\n   - Change `xunit` v2.9.3 to `xunit.v3` (latest v3 package)\n   - Change `YTest.MTP.XUnit2` to `YTest.MTP.XUnit3` (the MTP adapter for v3)\n   - The project SDK needs to change: xUnit v3 test projects should use `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` still, but they need to be an executable (OutputType Exe) since xUnit v3 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly\n   - For the runner integration, I should use `xunit.runner.visualstudio` v3 or rely on the built-in MTP support that comes with xUnit v3\n   - The `YTest.MTP.XUnit2` package likely has a v3 equivalent I need to identify, or I might need to check if it's compatible with v3 at all\n   - For the test code itself, the namespaces and attributes like `[Fact]` and `Assert` remain unchanged in v3, so `BasicTests.cs` shouldn't require modifications\n   - The real work is updating the `.csproj` file with the new package references and the executable output type that v3 requires the custom adapter or if it's built-in now. Let me just try restoring and building the project first to see what happens, then I can determine what other changes are needed for the migration.","outputTokens":1708,"requestId":"B829:373498:30B066E:3382EBE:6A049567"},"id":"10c9fd14-5555-4fbe-b680-319d7d178ed9","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:15:17.090Z","parentId":"51034d34-2612-429d-b32a-25b31a4392a7"}
